Londen mr. Kent
sence my last of 27 cur recd yours of 11d, I wonder you had not yett mine
of 13 with the severall remises of which I doubt must send seconds in case yours
next doth not advise mee their recept, with some remise as write before though
ena so low, yett lower here to have the advantage of remitting I see the patt
of 12, clothes bought & reddy to pack, butt what I want most not by for not
onep to 2 of 16 xber nor to 4 & 5 which I want most principally N2
therefore recommend you onee more said N214 & 5 & all then I ordered on
the 6 cur, I doe much wonder that you have not alreaddy 4 a 5 p to N2
of 16 xber, because I have writt you before that you might buy anney p
of anney prices when ever you meet that cull & where as, I want them
above all & N4 of 20 cur so must tellyou that you must proferse mel
this time, because I suppose you have manney orders for them cullours,
haveinge writt you so longe, before you ought not to give anney to others
before mine are compleated, the 12 patt you sent mee are all ordinarie culd
of which enonghare to be had, I recommend you onee more the spa clothes
& to send mee one pack where in the most demanded cloth by first convoy
if anney departs for holland before that for ostend for this fross holdinge
leutt will be att the dore before the goods can be here, as for reds &
whites if deare & scareis lett them there till you finde them to content
for though I could wish to have them yett to buy these goods 4 a 5
p c deurer then last yeare rather have theless, & butt ½ the quantitie
so pray minde my intrest & lett mee kxow from time to time, what
passer, doe what you can to have the northrens att hull aboard thes
convoy supposeinge you have goods then that you couserve mee
there or there about or that time will permitt duringe this frost
to gett them there though butt 5,6 a 8 p & that the 10 for
londen be ander wayt
